wikipedia_page.main: Peter Dyke (born 11 March 1965) is an English organist.  A Fellow of the Royal College of Organists, he has recorded several albums either as a soloist or accompanist, including three for Regent Records and one for Priory Records.

response: However, a breakdown in relationship with BDO chairman Olly Croft and the late Peter Dyke of Imperial Tobacco saw him exit the sport.  A situation mirrored when the world's top players broke away to form the rival Professional Darts Corporation.
